Key Match Events: David Miller scored an unbeaten 59 off 51 balls to give South Africa victory
Tristan Stubbs shared a stand of 65 with Miller
Sybrand Engelbrecht dismissed for 45 off 40 balls, turning out to be key
South Africa needed 27 off 22 balls when Stubbs was out, but Miller hit three sixes and a four
Miscellaneous Highlights: Netherlands won this fixture in the last T20 World Cup and in the ODI version last year
The Dutch came close to defeating South Africa but lost by four wickets
The result counts as an upset in a week full of them
Marco Jansen's height made him almost unplayable on the springy pitch
Anrich Nortje's pace was hardly any easier to face
Engelbrecht quit the sport in 2016 and took it up again on the weekends only after joining a finance company in the Netherlands
The game was held at Nassau County International Cricket Stadium
